<h2 style="text-align: center;">Student Application Instructions</h2>
<p>
In order to register for the Arizona Winter School, you will need to
create an account at mathprograms.org.  Please follow the instructions
below, noting especially that <b>you must submit a tailored letter request</b>,
rather than a generic letter request.

<p>

<ol>
<li>
  To start the application process, open <a href="https://www.mathprograms.org/db/112/841/apply">this link</a> in a new window.
  </li>
<li>
   Create an account with mathprograms.org, using your institutional email address.
  </li>
 <li>
  Fill out the standard cover sheet. 
  You must enter the name and contact information of your reference-writer (typically your advisor). <b>Leave the box "email notify writer on submit" un-checked.</b>
  </li>
   <li>
  After completing the cover sheet, proceed with your application through mathprograms by filling out
  all of the additional information requested.
  </li>
  <li>
  You must request a <b>tailored letter</b> from your
  reference writer. To do this, <b>click the green arrow</b>
  next to your reference's email address and mark the option <b>Request a tailored letter for this institution only</b>, then click <b>submit</b> in the dialogue box.

  <p>
  <img src="http://swc.math.arizona.edu/misc/local/ExhibitB1.png" alt="Click The Green Arrow"  width="600">
  </li>
<li>
  Click <b>apply</a>.
  </li>
</ol>

You will receive a confirmation from mathprograms.org.
Application and funding decisions will be made in December.


</div>
